21/03/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- A court Tuesday (March 20th) sentenced the mayor of Hakkari to prison for seven years for membership in the banned Kurdistan People's Party (PKK). 
Metin Tekce was also found guilty of denying that the PKK is a terrorist group. 
He had defended PKK in testimony before a parliamentary committee. 
He was convicted in absentia, and reportedly is in France.
In other news, Turkey is preparing to host the 5th World Water Forum in 2009. 
Some 300 delegates from 50 countries gathered in Istanbul on Tuesday to work on the agenda, which will focus on better managing water resources. 
(Reuters, AP - 20/03/07)
